headline: U.S. Bank: Freight market contracts in Q3 as capacity tightens
summary: MINNEAPOLIS, October 30, 2025--The U.S. truck freight market reversed its brief Q2 improvement in the third quarter of 2025, with national shipment volumes contracting 2.9%, according to the latest U.S. Bank Freight Payment Index. Meanwhile, shipper spending managed to increase for second consecutive quarter.
